To further study the exciton properties in ML perylene derivatives, we performed temperature-dependent optical measurements. Figure 3a shows the PL and differential reflectance (ΔR/R) spectrum of ML Me-PTCDI at 4 K (the same sample, on quartz substrate). The PL showed drastically reduced linewidth of 8.5 meV, little vibronic progression and nearly perfect linear polarization P=Imax−IminImax+Imin=94.1%\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
